23/09/2009
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Greece was the biggest net beneficiary of the EU's budget in 2008, according to the European Commission's 2008 financial report published on Tuesday (September 22nd).
The document shows that last year, Greece received a net of 6.187 billion euros from the EU's budget, most of which went to farmers and infrastructure projects.
Romania received 2.6 billion euros and paid 1.217 billion euros.
Bulgaria received almost 1 billion euros from the EU's funding last year under various pre-accession programmes.
The country also received compensation for contributing money to the EU budget before it actually started to assimilate any funding from the bloc.
(ANA-MPA, BNR, bTV, EC website - 22/09/09)
